Vice President Kamala Harris hosted President Cyril Ramaphosa of South Africa for breakfast at the Naval Observatory to highlight the strong partnership between the United States and South Africa. They discussed various topics including the global COVID-19 response, vaccine equity in Africa, global health and health security, collaboration through PEPFAR, tackling the climate crisis, space engagement, science and technology leadership, advancing the women, peace, and security agenda, and cooperating on matters of peace and security affecting the continent.